---
description:
Defines how every screen in LexMastery should be composed.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Screen Composition

Every screen follows a predictable layout.

Consistency reduces cognitive load.

---

# Screen Hierarchy

SafeArea

↓

Scaffold

↓

AppBar

↓

Body

↓

Bottom Action

↓

Snackbar/Dialog

Avoid deeply nested layouts.

---

# App Bar

Every screen should define:

Title

Back behavior

Primary action

Overflow actions

Avoid clutter.

---

# Body

Prefer:

Header

↓

Primary Content

↓

Supporting Content

↓

Primary CTA

Maintain generous spacing.

---

# Sections

Long pages should be divided into sections.

Every section should have:

Heading

Content

Optional action

---

# Scroll Behavior

Use CustomScrollView when combining:

Lists

Headers

Cards

Avoid nested scrolling.

---

# Empty Space

Whitespace improves comprehension.

Do not compress layouts.

---

# Primary Action

Every screen should have one obvious primary action.

Avoid competing CTAs.

---

# Floating Action Button

Only use FAB when it represents the primary action.

Otherwise prefer inline buttons.

---

# Bottom Sheets

Use for contextual actions.

Never replace entire screens with bottom sheets.

---

# Dialogs

Use dialogs only for:

Confirmation

Critical information

Irreversible actions

---

# Navigation

Every screen must define:

Entry point

Exit point

Back behavior

---

# Error Recovery

Every screen should support:

Loading

Empty

Error

Offline

Retry

---

# Cursor Instructions

Generate screens using consistent layout hierarchy.

Avoid inventing new layouts unless justified.